-- tf.h3: `Step 3`: Generate a live site for yourself

-- ftd.row:
width: fill-container

-- ftd.column:
width.fixed.percent: 50
align-content: right

-- tf.markdown:

- Go to `Settings` 

- Select `Pages`, from Table of Content

- Under Branch, click on the drop-down and select `gh-pages`

- Click on `Save`

This will build your GitHub pages and deploy your website.

To verify, go back to `Actions` and you will see 3 workflows now, the latest 
will be `pages and deployment`.

-- end: ftd.column


